#+title: Installing Emacs Notes
#+startup: showall indent
#+options: toc:nil

* Setup
** Install System Packages
#+begin_src
sudo apt install autoconf makeinfo texi2html texinfo libtiff-dev build-essential libgtk-3-dev libtiff5-dev libgif-dev libjpeg-dev libpng-dev libxpm-dev libncurses-dev libmagickwand-dev libcjson-dev libgnutls28-dev libjansson-dev libsystemd-dev
#+end_src
** Build and Install Emacs
#+begin_src
git clone https://git.savannah.gnu.org/git/emacs.git
cd emacs
git checkout emacs-28.0.92
./autogen.sh
./configure --with-mailutils --with-x-toolkit=gtk3 --with-imagemagick --with-json
make
sudo make install
#+end_src
- When checking out a new version, run =make distclean= to get to a clean state and reconfigure and remake

** Install packages for my configuration
*** Ripgrep
#+begin_src
cargo install ripgrep
#+end_src
*** Rtags
#+begin_src
sudo apt install llvm llvm-dev clang libclang-dev libssl-dev zlib1g-dev pkgconfig
cd ~/Code
git clone --recursive https://github.com/Andersbakken/rtags.git
cd rtags
cmake -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=1 .
make
sudo make install
#+end_src
*** Pdf tools
#+begin_src
sudo apt install libpng-dev zlib1g-dev libpoppler-glib-dev libpoppler-private-dev imagemagick
#+end_src
- It will give an error that it isn't installed
- Go to =init.el= and comment out the =:pin manual= line
  - This just make it so that it needs to manually be updated since it takes a while to update
*** Cscope
#+begin_src
sudo apt-get install cscope
#+end_src
*** Vterm
#+begin_src
sudo apt-get cmake libtool-bin
#+end_src
